    "media:imagetext": "1908\n1928\nOn December 31, 1908, exactly twenty years ago today-Wilbur Wright established a new. world's record for distance\nand duration covering 124.7 kilometers in two hours twenty minutes thirty-two and two-tenths seconds, winning the\nMichelin Trophy and other valuable prizes.\nThis epocha\nadiyegent marked the birth of aeria! tarsportation.\nMillville, Indiana postoffice has been discontinued, now\n* DEC 31\nsupplied by New Castle, Indiana, which is 5 miles from\nthe birthplace of Wilbur Wright.\nPM\n1928\nND:\nAIR.\n1867 Wright 1912\nThis\nCover\ndedicated\nto Wilbur Wright who\ndaringly\nand honorably\naldec\nand\nA18-\nMiliville,\nsent from\nIt. indian frone\nplace of his\nbirth.\nVIA AIR MAIL\nCAPT. B. B. LIPSNER\nAMERICA'S FIRST AIR MAIL SUP'T.\nCHICAGO",
